    "description": {
      "value": "<h1 class=\"title\">Fury drops</h1>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Source</strong> <em>Animal Archive pg. 13</em><br /><strong>Price</strong> 50 gp; <strong>Weight</strong> &mdash;<br /><strong>Category</strong> Alchemical Remedies</span></p>\n<h2 class=\"framing\">Description</h2><p>\n<p>Anointing a creature&rsquo;s eyes with a dose of fury drops causes it to immediately fly into a rage for 1d6 rounds, granting it a +2 alchemical bonus to Strength and Constitution, a +1 alchemical bonus on Will saves, and a -2 penalty to AC. The effect is otherwise identical to a barbarian&rsquo;s rage, and creatures are fatigued at the end of the rage. Only creatures with an Intelligence score of 1 or 2 can be affected by fury drops.</p>\n</p><h2 class=\"framing\">Construction</h2><p>\n<p><strong>Craft (Alchemy)</strong> DC 25</p>",
